  "texts": [
    "Let ρ H ∈ Hom(π 1 (B), Aut(N) δ ⋉ N) be a homomorphism and set M:= B × N. The diagonal right action of π 1 (B) on M given by (b,x)•γ = (b•γ, ρ H (γ -1)x) is properly discontinuous and M:= M /π 1 (B)is a twisted principal N-bundle over B, with twisting homomorphism ρ:= q • ρ H, where q: Aut(N) ⋉ N → Aut(N) is the 'quotient by N' projection.",
    "The trivial connection T B on M induces a connection H on M with monodromy ρ H. It is not hard to see that in fact we haveM = B × ρ H N.We note that flat connections always exist when N is contractible (in particular, for N simply-connected and nilpotent): Proposition 2.9.",
    "Let N be a contractible Lie group and let M be a twisted principal N-bundle with twisting homomorphism ρ: π 1 (B) → Aut(N).",
    "Then, there exists a flat connection H on M with monodromy ρ.",
    "Moreover, given such a connection, there is an isomorphism of flat twisted principal bundles M ≃ B × ρ N.Proof."
  ],
